hopobject.body: Can you hear me OK? doctoryourself.com The main risk of these funds is that although they reward investors when the stock market takes a hit, in good years they often lag significantly behind because the hedging strategy mutes returns. In other words, because each part of a particular fund's portfolio is designed to do well when another part fails, there's never an occasion when the entire portfolio is gaining at the same time.
